article.headline: Delaware State 63, Bethune Cookman 61
article.story: DAYTONA BEACH, Fla. (AP) -- Terrance Hunter hit a 14-foot fall-away jumper with two seconds left to give Delaware State a 63-61 win over Bethune-Cookman on Tuesday night. Hunter finished with 15 points and Jahsha Bluntt chipped in with 18 as the Hornets (9-11, 7-2 Mid-Eastern Athletic) won their fifth straight. Antonio Webb led Bethune-Cookman (9-11, 7-2) with 18 points and Michael Williams added 13. The game was tight throughout, with neither team leading by more than five points. Bethune-Cookman led 49-44 with 6:57 to play before Bluntt started an 8-2 run with a 3-pointer. Caheem Broadus gave the Hornets the lead with a basket with 5:19 left. The teams traded baskets the rest of the way, with Bethune-Cookman's Cleveland Williams hitting a shot to tie the game at 61 with 1:11 left. That set up Hunter, who had made only four of his previous 11 shots, hitting the game-winner from the free thrown line.
